1️⃣ Core Teaching (Simple, Exam-Oriented)
🔹 Who is the Vice President?

The Vice President of India is:

Second highest constitutional office

Ex-officio Chairman of Rajya Sabha

📌 Mentioned in Articles 63–71

🔵 Election of Vice President

Elected by:

Members of Parliament (Lok Sabha + Rajya Sabha)

Includes both elected and nominated members

📌 Difference from President election (very important).

🔹 Method of Election

Proportional Representation

Single Transferable Vote (STV)

🔴 Qualifications

To become Vice President:

Citizen of India

Minimum age: 35 years

Qualified for Rajya Sabha

No office of profit

🔹 Term & Removal

Term: 5 years

Removal:

By resolution in Rajya Sabha

Agreed by Lok Sabha

📌 No impeachment (unlike President).

🔹 Powers & Functions
1️⃣ As Vice President

Acts as President in absence of President

2️⃣ As Chairman of Rajya Sabha

Presides over Rajya Sabha sessions

Maintains order

Decides on procedural matters

📌 Does not vote normally, but can give casting vote in case of tie.

🔹 Important Differences (President vs Vice President)
Feature	President	Vice President
Election body	MPs + MLAs	MPs only
Nominated members vote	No	Yes
Removal	Impeachment	Resolution
Role	Head of State	RS Chairman
